        "Crushing possession dominance (80.8%) with 666 passes at 89% accuracy",
        "153 completed line breaks — highest penetration volume in match",
        "CALHANOGLU and BARDAKCI combining for 185 passes at near-perfect accuracy",
        "101 defensive pressures and 41 forced turnovers limiting Paraguay build-up"
      ],
      "weaknesses": [
        "Only 5 shots on target from 32 attempts — catastrophic conversion despite 2.13 xG",
        "Conceded at minute 2 from single counter before game started tactically",
        "Inability to break Paraguay 46-phase low-block despite vast territorial dominance",
        "Defensive transition vulnerability exposed despite dominant possession stats"
      ]
    },
    "PAR": {
      "summary": "Paraguay executed textbook counter-attacking masterclass in 4-2-3-1 low block, absorbing 80.8% Turkey possession and winning 1-0 through GALARZA 2nd-minute strike. With only 19.2% possession and 0.36 xG, result defied statistics completely.",
